File: Growthpoint, which has a stake in the V&A Waterfront, has seen a surge in arrears and provisions. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa’s largest property group Growthpoint is the latest company to have deferred a decision on a final dividend. This as COVID-19 weighs on the outlook for local landlords. The group, which has a stake in the V&A Waterfront, has seen a surge in arrears and provisions. READ: We Are Open: Western Cape ready to welcome tourists V&A has been the hardest hit by the travel bans and its recovery will depend on the resumption on international travel. Growthpoint has announced a 16 percent plunge in distributable income and an almost 50 percent drop in year-end profits. Local bad debt writeoffs and provisions rocketed to R236-million from R19-million previously.